Vice President Biden spoke with Colombian President Juan Manuel Santos to congratulate the Colombian government on the recent breakthrough in peace negotiations with the Revolutionary Armed Forces of Colombia (FARC). They discussed the main elements of the peace accords, including transitional justice and the demobilization, disarmament, and reintegration of combatants. Biden pledged his strong personal commitment and the support of the United States for the successful implementation of the peace accords. They also discussed the importance of maintaining bipartisan support for Colombia in the United States Congress. They agreed that for peace to be sustainable, it must include meaningful justice for victims, extension of the rule of law and government services, and education, jobs, and economic opportunities. Biden also expressed his support for Colombia's important regional leadership and the ongoing Pacific Alliance summit in Chile.